  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200\u00b0C (400\u00b0F).",
    "In a large bowl, combine diced potatoes, grated carrot, diced bell pepper, and crushed rice crackers.",
    "Add beaten egg, furikake, chopped nori, sesame seeds, tamari, rice vinegar, sesame oil, salt, and pepper to the bowl; toss until all ingredients are evenly coated.",
    "Spread the mixture in an 8x8-inch baking dish, pressing down lightly to create an even layer.",
    "Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the potatoes are tender.",
    "Remove from oven and let it rest for 5 minutes before slicing.",
    "Serve warm as a satisfying lunch or side dish.",
    "Enjoy the fresh crunch and subtle umami flavors."
  ],
